Thousands of people navigate the busy streets of Cape Town every day, yet very few know about the mysterious world beneath them. In the first part of a new series exploring hidden and forgotten places, News24 takes you underground into a network of tunnels under the city. Tour guide Matt Weisse, one of the few people who has explored the 20km of tunnels, explains their origins and purpose over the centuries. WATCH | 91-year-old grandpa graduate gets PhD, says he's not done yet! Andries Conradie, a 91-year-old great-grandfather, recently became the oldest man to obtain his doctorate at Unisa - and, he is not quite done yet. Watch.